  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">Lower Manhattan</span><span class="entry-tag">Tower</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">1,776 feet. Square base chamfers into eight isosceles triangles at mid-height, generating an octagonal shaft that tapers upward. The relationship between the tower, the memorial pools, and the surrounding campus is the more interesting spatial study.</p>
