  <p class="entry-blurb">Student center for Columbia. A sequence of glass-enclosed ramps rises through a central atrium — the section is the project. Tschumi's theoretical preoccupations with event, movement, and program are built into the circulation structure. The ramps are not efficient; that is the point.</p>
