  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">Upper East Side</span><span class="entry-tag">Museum</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">Continuous quarter-mile spiral ramp descending from a 92-foot skylit rotunda. Rejects the sequential gallery model entirely. Ramp walls tilt outward — Wright intended paintings displayed at an easel angle. 21 artists protested before it opened.</p>
