  <p class="entry-blurb">60-story residential tower. Each floor plate shifts and cantilevers independently, producing a stacked, Jenga-like profile. No two floors are identical. The cantilevered bay windows are structural — the shifts are not cladding but floor slabs. 145 units across 821 feet.</p>
  <a class="map-link" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=56+Leonard+St,+New+York,+NY+10013" target="_blank">↗ 56 Leonard St</a>
</div>

