  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">Bowery, Lower East Side</span><span class="entry-tag">Museum</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">Seven stacked aluminum mesh volumes, each shifted off-center. The exterior skin is anodized expanded aluminum that diffuses light and changes with weather and time of day. The shifts create irregular floor heights suited to large-scale contemporary work. Kazuyo Sejima and Ryue Nishizawa won the Pritzker Prize three years later, in 2010.</p>
  <a class="map-link" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=235+Bowery,+New+York,+NY+10002" target="_blank">↗ 235 Bowery</a>
