  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">Midtown — Museum Mile</span><span class="entry-tag">Residential Tower</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">1,050-foot residential tower cantilevering over MoMA's rooftop. The exposed diagonal structural bracing becomes the primary facade element — the frame is the building. Nouvel initially rejected the commission; the structural engineering constraints of building over an operating museum produced the formal language. Note: the tower's relationship to MoMA's public mission is a point of legitimate critical debate.</p>
