<div class="entry" data-type="civic" data-hood="midtown" data-arch="warren">
  <div class="img-slot" data-wiki="Grand_Central_Terminal"><span>Add image</span></div>
  <div class="entry-row"><span class="entry-label">Warren &amp; Wetmore + Reed &amp; Stem</span><span class="entry-cost">1913</span></div>
  <h2 class="entry-title">Grand Central Terminal</h2>
  <div class="icons"><span class="icon icon-landmark">Landmark</span><span class="icon icon-iconic">⊙ Iconic</span></div>
  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">Midtown, 42nd St</span><span class="entry-tag">Civic + Infrastructure</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">Beaux-Arts, 1913. The Main Concourse: 275 feet long, 120 feet wide, 125 feet high — the celestial ceiling (2,500 stars, painted cerulean) originally faced backwards, a theological convention placing the viewer inside the sphere of heaven. 44 platforms across two levels. Saved from demolition in 1978 by a landmark preservation campaign led in part by Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis. Free and open daily.</p>
  <a class="map-link" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=89+E+42nd+St,+New+York,+NY+10017" target="_blank">↗ 89 E 42nd St</a>
</div>

<div class="entry" data-type="civic" data-hood="midtown" data-arch="warren">
  <div class="img-slot" data-wiki="Rockefeller_Center"><span>Add image</span></div>
