  <div class="entry-row"><span class="entry-label">McKim Mead &amp; White + Kevin Roche</span><span class="entry-cost">1902–1990</span></div>
  <h2 class="entry-title">The Metropolitan Museum of Art</h2>
  <div class="icons"><span class="icon icon-landmark">Landmark</span><span class="icon icon-iconic">⊙ Iconic</span></div>
  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">Upper East Side</span><span class="entry-tag">Museum</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">The Fifth Avenue facade by McKim, Mead &amp; White, completed 1902, is a Beaux-Arts screen in front of a Victorian Gothic building by Calvert Vaux. Kevin Roche John Dinkeloo &amp; Associates added the American Wing (1980), Sackler Wing (1978), and Lila Acheson Wallace Wing (1987). The building is the institution's most complex artifact. 17 acres of floor space across five city blocks.</p>
  <a class="map-link" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=1000+5th+Ave,+New+York,+NY+10028" target="_blank">↗ 1000 5th Ave</a>
</div>

<div class="entry" data-type="civic" data-hood="midtown" data-arch="mckim">
  <div class="img-slot" data-wiki="New_York_Public_Library"><span>Add image</span></div>
