  <div class="entry-row"><span class="entry-label">Farmers Market</span><span class="entry-cost">Free entry</span></div>
  <h2 class="entry-title">Union Square Greenmarket</h2>
  <div class="icons"><span class="icon icon-iconic">⊙ Iconic</span><span class="icon icon-free">Free</span></div>
  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">Union Square — Mon / Wed / Fri / Sat</span><span class="entry-tag">Year-round, 8am–6pm</span><span class="entry-tag">Since 1976</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">GrowNYC, since 1976. Up to 140 regional farmers, fishers, and bakers. The largest and oldest farmers market in NYC and one of the great public markets in the United States. Saturday is peak — 60,000 visitors. Heritage meats, farmstead cheese, artisan bread, cut flowers, ciders, maple. The market played a documented role in the revitalization of Union Square from the late 1970s onward.</p>
  <a class="map-link" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Union+Square+Greenmarket,+New+York,+NY" target="_blank">↗ Union Square Park, North + West sides</a>
</div>

<div class="entry" data-type="market event" data-cuisine="" data-cost="$" data-hood="bushwick-greenpoint">
