  <div class="entry-row"><span class="entry-label">Food Market</span><span class="entry-cost">Free entry</span></div>
  <h2 class="entry-title">Smorgasburg</h2>
  <div class="icons"><span class="icon icon-iconic">⊙ Iconic</span><span class="icon icon-free">Free</span></div>
  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">Sat — Williamsburg Waterfront / Sun — Prospect Park</span><span class="entry-tag">May–October + WTC Thu/Fri year-round</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">Jonathan Butler and Eric Demby (Brooklyn Flea founders), 2011. 100+ independent food vendors. The Williamsburg waterfront Saturday location is the original and best — East River views, eclectic vendor mix. Ramen burgers, miso-honey wings, Filipino BBQ, natural wine, artisan ice cream. The place where NYC food trends start.</p>
  <a class="map-link" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Smorgasburg+Williamsburg,+Brooklyn,+NY" target="_blank">↗ Williamsburg Waterfront (Sat)</a>
</div>

<div class="entry" data-type="market event" data-cuisine="" data-cost="$" data-hood="brooklyn">
