  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">Broadway &amp; 12th St</span><span class="entry-tag">Since 1927</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">18 miles of books. Founded 1927, still independent. Three floors plus basement. $1 outdoor carts on the Broadway sidewalk. Strongest used sections: art, design, photography, literature. New York Magazine's third-largest book buyer in the city after Barnes &amp; Noble and McNally Jackson.</p>
  <a class="map-link" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=828+Broadway,+New+York,+NY+10003" target="_blank">↗ 828 Broadway at 12th St</a>
</div>

<div class="entry" data-type="shopping books" data-cuisine="" data-cost="$" data-hood="nolita-soho">
