  <p class="entry-blurb">Started as a pushcart rug business on the Lower East Side in 1897. Now a six-floor Flatiron emporium — rugs, furniture, textiles, lighting, objects. The rug collection is the primary draw; handmade pieces from every major weaving tradition. A genuine institution.</p>
