  <h2 class="entry-title">Baker House</h2>
  <div class="icons"><span class="icon icon-landmark">Landmark</span></div>
  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">MIT Campus</span><span class="entry-tag">Residential</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">Senior dormitory on the Charles River. The serpentine plan — Aalto's only built example of the form at this scale — maximizes river views from each room while creating a concave court on the campus side. Load-bearing brick exterior with deeply recessed windows. Aalto's first American commission.</p>
  <a class="map-link" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=362+Memorial+Dr,+Cambridge,+MA+02139" target="_blank">↗ 362 Memorial Dr</a>
</div>

<div class="entry" data-type="civic" data-hood="harvard" data-arch="andrews">
  <div class="img-slot" data-wiki="Gund_Hall"><span>Add image</span></div>
  <div class="entry-row"><span class="entry-label">Andrews, John</span><span class="entry-cost">1972</span></div>
  <h2 class="entry-title">Gund Hall — Harvard GSD</h2>
  <div class="icons"><span class="icon icon-landmark">Landmark</span></div>
  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">Harvard, Cambridge</span><span class="entry-tag">Civic + Academic</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">A single stepped trayshed — a continuous glass-roofed studio floor cascading in four tiers from top to ground — houses all design disciplines in one shared space. The section is the building's entire argument. At night it reads as a lantern.</p>
  <a class="map-link" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=48+Quincy+St,+Cambridge,+MA+02138" target="_blank">↗ 48 Quincy St</a>
</div>

<div class="entry" data-type="civic" data-hood="harvard" data-arch="corbusier">
  <div class="img-slot" data-wiki="Carpenter_Center_for_the_Visual_Arts"><span>Add image</span></div>
  <div class="entry-row"><span class="entry-label">Corbusier, Le</span><span class="entry-cost">1963</span></div>
  <h2 class="entry-title">Carpenter Center for the Visual Arts</h2>
  <div class="icons"><span class="icon icon-landmark">Landmark</span></div>
  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">Harvard, Cambridge</span><span class="entry-tag">Civic + Academic</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">The only building Le Corbusier completed in North America. A ramp bisects the building at the third floor, connecting two streets through the mass of the structure. Brise-soleil on all elevations; pilotis lifting the mass off the ground. Béton brut.</p>
  <a class="map-link" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=24+Quincy+St,+Cambridge,+MA+02138" target="_blank">↗ 24 Quincy St</a>
</div>

<div class="entry" data-type="museum" data-hood="boston" data-arch="dsr">
  <div class="img-slot" data-wiki="Institute_of_Contemporary_Art,_Boston"><span>Add image</span></div>
  <div class="entry-row"><span class="entry-label">Diller Scofidio + Renfro</span><span class="entry-cost">2006</span></div>
  <h2 class="entry-title">Institute of Contemporary Art</h2>
  <div class="icons"><span class="icon icon-landmark">Landmark</span></div>
  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">South Boston Waterfront</span><span class="entry-tag">Museum</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">Cantilevered volume extending 80 feet over the harbor. The main gallery projects beyond the building's footprint to hover above the water. A wooden amphitheater beneath forms a sheltered public space. The ground floor is transparent; the harbor reads through the building from the street.</p>
  <a class="map-link" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=25+Harbor+Shore+Dr,+Boston,+MA+02210" target="_blank">↗ 25 Harbor Shore Dr</a>
</div>

<div class="entry" data-type="civic" data-hood="mit" data-arch="gehry">
  <div class="img-slot" data-wiki="Ray_and_Maria_Stata_Center"><span>Add image</span></div>
  <div class="entry-row"><span class="entry-label">Gehry Partners</span><span class="entry-cost">2004</span></div>
