  <h2 class="entry-title">John Hancock Tower (200 Clarendon)</h2>
  <div class="icons"><span class="icon icon-landmark">Landmark</span></div>
  <p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-tag">Back Bay</span><span class="entry-tag">Tower</span></p>
  <p class="entry-blurb">60-story parallelogram in blue reflective glass, designed by Henry Cobb. The parallelogram floor plan with a geometric notch at each narrow side allows the tower to read as an almost impossibly thin plane from certain angles. 500-pound glass panes detached during construction; complete reglazing required. Two 300-ton tuned mass dampers on the 58th floor.</p>
  <a class="map-link" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=200+Clarendon+St,+Boston,+MA+02116" target="_blank">↗ 200 Clarendon St</a>
</div>

<div class="entry" data-type="civic" data-hood="dorchester" data-arch="pei">
